                        Ʋzziah ſought the Lord, and God made him to proſper, and helped him againſt his Enemies, and made the Philiſtines, Arabiaas and Ammonites, Tributaries to him;

but he grew proud with the Succeſs that was given him, and invaded the Prieſts Office, and aſſumed to offer Incenſe in the Temple; for which he was a Leper to the day of his Death, and was depoſed the Kingdom, and his Son Jotham reigned in his ſtead, 2 Chron. 26. and 2 King. 1.5.
